@node Objects.About "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@prev Objects.About
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - About


            This option displays the current version of the Modeler program,
        along with the amount of free memory available to the system.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.New "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - New


            This option will reset most of the Modeler to its original
        defaults. All layers and objects will be cleared. If this option
        is used, any objects not saved will be lost. This option may not
        clear some of the submenus in the Modeler.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Load "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Load


            This will load a new Lightwave object into the Modeler. The
        object must be in Lightwave format, and will be loaded into the
        first layer. To load an object of another format, either import
        it from the Modeler, or convert it to Lightwave format using a
        program such as Pixel 3D or Interchange.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.L }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Layer     @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.L }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Load      @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Save "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Save


            This is used to save the currently selected layers to disk
        as one object. The object will use the origin as its center,
        used when rotating the object. The name of the file will be the
        name cuurently used since loading the object. To save the object
        as a different name, use the Save As command. Although the object
        may be in numerous layers or parts, the entire layer or group of
        layers will be stored as one layer.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.L }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Layer     @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.O }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Object    @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.S }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Save      @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Save_As "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Save As


            This is similar to the Save command, yet allows the currently
        selected objects and layers to be saved under a different name than
        originally used when loading the object.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.L }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Layer     @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.O }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Object    @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.S }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Save      @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Import "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Import


            This is used to import an object from the Layout editor. The
        objects currently loaded into the Layout editor will be listed in
        a menu. This can be used when loading objects in formats other than
        the Lightwave 3D format, which the Modeler may not be able to load.
        Any object imported into the Modeler will be loaded into the current
        layer. All other existing layers will remain unchanged.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.I }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Import   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Export "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Export


            This option is used to transfer a newly modeled object or a
        modified object into the Layout editor. If the object exists in
        the Layout editor, then it will be listed in the Export submenu.
        If it does not exist, you must select the << NEW >>> menu item.
        This will allow you to transfer a new object into the Layout editor
        as well as save a copy of the object on disk.
            If an object is already in the Layout editor, and a modified
        version is exported to the Layout editor, it will not be stored
        on disk. The modified will have to be saved from either the Modeler
        or the Layout editor.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.E }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Export   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Macro "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Macro

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.M }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Macro   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Box "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Box


            This is used to create three dimensional squares or rectangles
        in the Modeler. After selecting this command, click the mouse
        pointer in one of the planar view windows and a small square will
        appear. Make a second click to define the shape and size of the
        box. Make a third click in one of the other two planar views to
        create the third dimension of the box. These dimensions may be
        altered before the box is actually created simply by reclicking
        near the desired corner of the box that you wish to modify. When
        satisfied with the box, select the Make command from the menu.

            @{"     " link Objects.Numeric  } Objects - Numeric
            @{"     " link Objects.Make     } Objects - Make

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Ball "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Ball


            This is used to create three dimensional balls or spheres
        in the Modeler. After selecting this command, click the mouse
        pointer in one of the planar view windows and a small square will
        appear. Make a second click to define the shape and size of the
        ball. Make a third click in one of the other two planar views to
        create the third dimension of the ball. These dimensions may be
        altered before the ball is actually created simply by reclicking
        near the desired corner of the box that you wish to modify. When
        satisfied with the ball, select the Make command from the menu.

            @{"     " link Objects.Numeric  } Objects - Numeric
            @{"     " link Objects.Make     } Objects - Make

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Disc "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Disc


            This is used to create discs or three dimensional cylinders
        in the Modeler. After selecting this command, click the mouse
        pointer in one of the planar view windows and a small square will
        appear. Make a second click to define the shape and size of the
        box. Make a third click in one of the other two planar views to
        create the third dimension of the cylinder, if desired. These
        dimensions may be altered before the disc is actually created simply
        by reclicking near the desired corner of the disc that you wish to
        modify. When satisfied with the disc or cylinder, select the Make
        command from the menu.

            @{"     " link Objects.Numeric  } Objects - Numeric
            @{"     " link Objects.Make     } Objects - Make

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Cone "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Cone


            This is used to create discs or three dimensional cones
        in the Modeler. After selecting this command, click the mouse
        pointer in one of the planar view windows and a small square will
        appear. Make a second click to define the shape and size of the
        box. Make a third click in one of the other two planar views to
        create the third dimension of the cone, if desired. These dimensions
        may be altered before the disc is actually created simply by
        reclicking near the desired corner of the disc that you wish to
        modify. When satisfied with the disc or cone, select the Make command
        from the menu.

            @{"     " link Objects.Numeric  } Objects - Numeric
            @{"     " link Objects.Make     } Objects - Make

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Sketch "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Sketch

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Numeric "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Numeric


            This is used to alter precise values regarding the size and
        location of the selected objects. This is also used to modify
        other values that are unique to the given objects or commands.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Make "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Make


            This option is used to actually create the object designed
        with the primitive tools. Lightwave allows the user to modify the
        exact specifications of the primitives without actually creating
        the object. For example, to form a cube, the user would drag the
        size of the cube on the editing window. This primitive may have
        its size altered by dragging the corners of the image. The Make
        button would be used to actually define the points and polygons
        needed for the object.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Text "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Text

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Objects.Options "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@next Objects.Options
@toc Modeler.Objects

    Objects - Options

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


