@prev Modeler.Objects
@next Modeler.Multiply
@toc Main

    Modeler - Modify

        @{"     " link Modify.Move      } Move
        @{"     " link Modify.Rotate    } Rotate
        @{"     " link Modify.Size      } Size
        @{"     " link Modify.Stretch   } Stretch
        @{"     " link Modify.Drag      } Drag
        @{"     " link Modify.Shear     } Shear
        @{"     " link Modify.Twist     } Twist
        @{"     " link Modify.Taper_1   } Taper 1
        @{"     " link Modify.Taper_2   } Taper 2
        @{"     " link Modify.Bend      } Bend
        @{"     " link Modify.Magnet    } Magnet
        @{"     " link Modify.Vortex    } Vortex
        @{"     " link Modify.Pole_1    } Pole 1
        @{"     " link Modify.Pole_2    } Pole 2
        @{"     " link Modify.Numeric   } Numeric

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Move "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@prev Modify.Move
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Move


            This is used to move an object or its parts to another
        location in the Modeler, within the same layer. First select
        an object, polygon, points, or volume. Then select the Move
        command, and hold the mouse button on one of the planar views
        while dragging it in the desired direction. The selected parts
        will move the same distance and direction as the mouse is
        dragged. These parts may be moved in any of the three planar
        views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Drag      } Modify - Drag
            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric   } Modify - Numeric
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.D }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Drag   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Rotate "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Rotate


            This is used to rotate an object or its parts around an
        axis in the Modeler, within the same layer. First select
        an object, polygon, points, or volume. Then select the Rotate
        command, and hold the mouse button on one of the planar views
        while dragging it in the desired direction. The selected parts
        will rotate about the axis where the mouse was initially clicked
        at as the mouse is dragged. These parts may be rotated in any of
        the three planar views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.R }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Rotate   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Size "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Size


            This is used to resize an object or its parts about its axis
        in the Modeler, within the same layer. First select an object,
        polygon, points, or volume. Then select the Size command, and hold
        the mouse button on one of the planar views while dragging it in
        the desired direction. The selected parts will become larger if
        the mouse is moved to the right, and they will become smaller if
        moved to the left. These parts will be resized in all of the three
        planar views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Stretch  } Modify - Stretch
            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Stretch "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Stretch


            This is used to resize an object or its parts about an axis
        in the Modeler, within the same layer. First select an object,
        polygon, points, or volume. Then select the Stretch command, and
        hold the mouse button on one of the planar views while dragging
        it in the desired direction. The size of the object will change
        depending on how the mouse is dragged, growing either larger or
        smaller. Only two of the three axes will be affected using this
        command, as opposed to using the Size command. These parts will
        be resized in all of the three planar views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Size      } Modify - Size
            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric   } Modify - Numeric

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Drag "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Drag


            This is used to move a point or multiple points to another
        location in the Modeler, within the same layer. Any point in the
        three planar views may be moved simply by selecting the point
        and dragging it to a new location. If multiple points are aligned
        under the same pointer location, each point will be dragged. If you
        wish to limit the points that may be dragged to a specific polygon
        or volume, you may selected the polygon or points before using
        the Drag command. This will only allow those preselected points to
        be dragged, although they need not be. The selected points will
        move the same distance and direction as the mouse is dragged.
        These points may be moved in any of the three planar views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Move      } Modify - Move
            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric   } Modify - Numeric
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.D }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Drag   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Shear "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Shear


            This is used to slant a polygon or multiple polygons in
        relation to the selected group of polygons. Any axis in the
        three planar views may be sheared simply by selecting that
        view and dragging the mouse. The effect of shearing will be
        reflected in the other planar views as well as the current
        planar view.

            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Twist "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Twist


            This is used to twist a polygon or multiple polygons in
        relation to the selected group of polygons. Any axis in the
        three planar views may be twisted simply by selecting that
        view and dragging the mouse. The effect of twisting will be
        reflected in the other planar views as well as the current
        planar view. Objects are twisted about the point initially
        selected by the mouse pointer in any of the planar views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Taper_1 "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Taper 1


            This is used to taper a polygon or multiple polygons in
        relation to the selected group of polygons. Any axis in the
        three planar views may be tapered simply by selecting that
        view and dragging the mouse. The effect of tapering will be
        reflected in the other planar views as well as the current
        planar view. Objects are tapered about the point initially
        selected by the mouse pointer in any of the planar views.
        All polygons are tapered proportional to the mouse pointer
        movement across one axis, unlike Taper 2.

            @{"     " link Modify.Taper_2  } Modify - Taper 2
            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Taper_2 "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Taper 2


            This is used to taper a polygon or multiple polygons in
        relation to the selected group of polygons. Any axis in the
        three planar views may be tapered simply by selecting that
        view and dragging the mouse. The effect of tapering will be
        reflected in the other planar views as well as the current
        planar view. Objects are tapered about the point initially
        selected by the mouse pointer in any of the planar views.
        All polygons are tapered proportional to the mouse pointer
        movement across two axes, unlike Taper 1.

            @{"     " link Modify.Taper_1  } Modify - Taper 1
            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Bend "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Bend


            This is used to bend a polygon or multiple polygons in
        relation to the selected group of polygons. Any axis in the
        three planar views may be bent simply by selecting that
        view and dragging the mouse. The effect of bending will be
        reflected in the other planar views as well as the current
        planar view. Objects are bent about the point initially
        selected by the mouse pointer in any of the planar views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Magnet "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Magnet


            This is used to push or pull a group of points in an
        object magnetically. This is done by creating a magnetic area
        of influence or by preselecting a group of points which may
        be modified. The area of magnetic influence may be created
        by selecting the three planar views with the left mouse button,
        by dragging a box at its corners. The box may also be dragged
        without modifying its shape by dragging the handle at the
        ceneter of the box. Points within the magnetic area may be
        pushed or pulled by dragging with the right mouse button. The
        points will be pushed or pulled towards the hidden mouse pointer.

            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.M} @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Magnetism   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Vortex "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Vortex


            This is used to create a vortex effect, or inward spiral,
        on an object or group of points. This is done by creating an
        area of influence which includes the objects or points to be
        modified. First drag a box using the left mouse button in the
        desired planar views. Points within the area may be modified
        by selecting a central point using the right mouse button and
        then dragging the mouse as the points are spun about the eye
        of the vortex.

            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.M} @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Vortex   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Pole_1 "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Pole 1


            This is used to resize an object or its parts about an axis
        in the Modeler, within the same layer. This is done by creating an
        area of influence which includes the objects or points to be
        modified. First drag a box using the left mouse button in the
        desired planar views. The size of the object within that area will
        change depending on how the mouse is dragged, growing either larger
        or smaller. Only one of the three axes will be affected using this
        command, as opposed to using the Pole 2 command. These parts will
        be resized in all of the three planar views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Pole_2   } Modify - Pole 2
            @{"     " link Modify.Size     } Modify - Size
            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.M} @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Resize   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Pole_2 "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Pole 2


            This is used to stretch an object or its parts about an axis
        in the Modeler, within the same layer. This is done by creating an
        area of influence which includes the objects or points to be
        modified. First drag a box using the left mouse button in the
        desired planar views. The size of the object within that area will
        change depending on how the mouse is dragged, growing either larger
        or smaller. Two of the three axes will be affected using this
        command, as opposed to using the Pole 1 command. These parts will
        be resized in all of the three planar views.

            @{"     " link Modify.Pole_1   } Modify - Pole 1
            @{"     " link Modify.Stretch  } Modify - Stretch
            @{"     " link Modify.Numeric  } Modify - Numeric
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.M} @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Stretch   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Modify.Numeric "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@next Modify.Numeric
@toc Modeler.Modify

    Modify - Numeric


            This is used to alter precise values regarding the size and
        location of the selected objects. This is also used to modify
        other values that are unique to the given objects or commands.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


