@node Tools.Drill "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@prev Tools.Drill
@toc Modeler.Tools

    Tools - Drill

            @{"     " link Tools.S_Drill                           } Tools - S Drill
            @{"     " link Tools.Boolean                           } Tools - Boolean
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Boolean    @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.D}@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Drill      @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Tools.S_Drill "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Tools

    Tools - S Drill


            This is used to perform drill operations on the current layer
        and a background layer. The current layer appears in gray and white,
        while the background layer appears in black. These layers contain
        3D objects which appear to be intersecting each other when both
        layers are visible. Upon performing a given drill function, the
        background layer will remain the same while the current layer will
        become modified depending on how the objects and layers intersect.
        This may involve removing excess portions of the current layer,
        depending on the operation.

            CORE    All remaining portions that are within the drilling
                    layer will be preserved in the current layer. All
                    portions of the current layer exterior to the drilling
                    tool will be discarded. Each intersection of the
                    current layer with the drilling tool will become
                    a point in the current layer, forming new points
                    as necessary.

            SLICE   All portions of the current layer are preserved, yet
                    any intersections with the drilling object will become
                    a point in the current layer, forming new points
                    as necessary.

            TUNNEL  All remaining portions that are exterior to the
                    drilling layer will be preserved in the current layer,
                    while all portions within the drilling object will
                    be discarded. Each intersection of the current layer
                    with the drilling tool will become a point in the
                    current layer, forming new points as necessary.

            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.sdrill SDrill'"                } ILBM: SDrill
            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.sdrill.core SDrill_Core'"      } ILBM: SDrill Core
            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.sdrill.slice SDrill_Slice'"    } ILBM: SDrill Slice
            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.sdrill.tunnel SDrill_Tunnel'"  } ILBM: SDrill Tunnel
            @{"     " link Tools.Drill                             } Tools - Drill
            @{"     " link Tools.Boolean                           } Tools - Boolean
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Boolean    @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.D}@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Drill      @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Tools.Boolean "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Tools

    Tools - Boolean


            This is used to perform boolean operations on the current layer
        and a background layer. The current layer appears in gray and white,
        while the background layer appears in black. These layers contain
        3D objects which appear to be intersecting each other when both
        layers are visible. Upon performing a given boolean function, the
        background layer will remain the same while the current layer will
        become modified depending on how the objects and layers intersect.
        This may involve removing excess portions of the current layer,
        depending on the operation.

            ADD         All portions of the current layer and drilling
                        layer will be combined to form a new object in
                        the current layer. Any intersecting polygons or
                        points will be reconstructed to form new polygons
                        about the surface of hollow objects.

            INTERSECT   Any portion of the current layer within the
                        drilling layer will be preserved, while any
                        portion exterior to the drilling layer will
                        be discarded. All intersections will be formed
                        with new points and polygons to form a new
                        surface for hollow objects.

            SUBTRACT    Any portion of the current layer exterior to
                        the drilling layer will be preserved, while any
                        portion within the drilling layer will be
                        discarded. All intersections will be formed with
                        new points and polygons to form a new surface for
                        hollow objects.

            UNION       Any portion of the current layer within the
                        drilling layer will be discarded, while any
                        portion exterior to the drilling layer will
                        be preserved, combined with any portion of the
                        drilling layer that is exterior to the current
                        layer. All intersections will be formed with new
                        points and polygons to form a new surface for
                        hollow objects.

            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.bool Boolean'"                 } ILBM: Boolean
            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.bool.add Boolean_Add'"         } ILBM: Boolean Add
            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.bool.int Boolean_Intersect'"   } ILBM: Boolean Intersect
            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.bool.sub Boolean_Subtract'"    } ILBM: Boolean Subtract
            @{"     " rxs "address command 'display.s 197 210 pictures/pic.tools.bool.union Boolean_Union'"     } ILBM: Boolean Union
            @{"     " link Tools.Drill                             } Tools - Drill
            @{"     " link Tools.S_Drill                           } Tools - S Drill
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.B}@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Boolean    @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.D}@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Drill      @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Tools.Merge "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Tools

    Tools - Merge


            This is used to remove duplicate points or to merge points
        that are reasonably close. This will make many objects look
        much cleaner, along with reducing rendering time, memory usage,
        and improve some rendering techniques. This is unlike the Polygon
        Merge command which is used to combine polygons together.

            @{"     " link Polygon.Merge} Polygon - Merge
            @{"     " link Polygon.Merge} Polygon - Unify

@endnode
