@node Display.Magnify "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@prev Display.Magnify
@toc Modeler.Display

    Display - Magnify


            This option is used to alter the size of the display for
        each of the given windows in the Modeler. The size of the grid
        will become larger or smaller as it is magnified. When the grid
        reaches its threshold, new grid sizes will appear. The objects
        will become magnified along with the grid. The actual size and
        measurements of the objects will not change, but the way it
        appears on the screen will. All windows will be magnified equally.
            Click on one of the views to magnify. To enlarge the images,
        move the mouse to the right. To reduce the images, move the mouse
        to the left. This is similar to the In and Out options. However,
        Magnify will alter the size of the display based on any part of
        the display, while the others will magnify the display based upon
        the center of the display.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.M }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Magnify   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Display.Pan "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Display

    Display - Pan


            This option is used move the display horizontally or vertically.
        The objects themselves will not be moved in relation to the grid,
        nor will they be moved in relation to each other. The only part
        affected will be the actaul display of the objects and not the
        actual coordinates of the objects.
            To move the display, click on any of the views in the Modeler.
        Then move the mouse in the direction that you wish to slide the
        display. The display can be moved at any time by pressing the ALT
        key and then dragging the display.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.P }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Pan   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Display.Measure "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Display

    Display - Measure

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Display.In "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Display

    Display - In


            This option is used to zoom into the display area for each of
        the windows in the Modeler. The display area will become magnified,
        but the objects themselves will not change in size. All display
        windows will be scaled equally. The display will zoom into the
        center of the display.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.Z }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Zoom   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Display.Out "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Display

    Display - Out


            This option is used to zoom out of the display area for each of
        the windows in the Modeler. The display area will become smaller,
        but the objects themselves will not change in size. All display
        windows will be scaled equally. The display will zoom out of the
        center of the display.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.Z }@{FG HIGHLIGHT } Zoom   @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Display.Fit_All "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Display

    Display - Fit All


            This option will scale the display in the window such that
        all objects are displayed in all three windows in whole. No
        portions of the objects will be hidden from view. This option
        works best when all three views are of equal size. Otherwise,
        the display will be scaled based upon the smallest dimensions
        of each axis.

            @{"     " link Display.Fit_Select      } Display - Fit Select

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Display.Fit_Select "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Display

    Display - Fit Select


            This option will scale the display in the window such that
        all currently selected objects will be displayed in all three
        windows. No portions of the selected objects will be hidden from
        view. If the views are of different sizes, the display will be
        scaled to fit the smallest dimensions of each axis.

            @{"     " link Display.Fit_All      } Display - Fit All

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Display.Options "Lightwave 3D - Modeler"
@toc Modeler.Display

    Display - Options


            ORIENTATION     Specifies how the planar views and preview
                            window will appear on the Modeler screen.

            PREVIEW         Specifies how the preview window will display
                            objects in the current layer.

            VISIBILITY      Specifies which types of parts are to be
                            visible in the Modeler.

            UNIT SYSTEM     Specifies which measurement units are to be
                            used in calculating sizes and distances in
                            the Modeler.

            GRID UNITS      Specifies the size of the grid drawn onto the
                            background of the Modeler planar views.

            GRID SNAP       Specifies how points are to be incremented
                            or scaled to the background grid in the
                            Modeler.

            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.G}@{FG HIGHLIGHT} Grid                @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.G}@{FG HIGHLIGHT} Grid Snap           @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.L}@{FG HIGHLIGHT} Layer               @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.P}@{FG HIGHLIGHT} Planar View         @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.P}@{FG HIGHLIGHT} Preview Window      @{FG TEXT}
            @{"     " link AORM.Glossary/Glossary.U}@{FG HIGHLIGHT} Units of Measure    @{FG TEXT}

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


